WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.380
Luke chapter number 10, Luke chapter number 10 this evening.

00:00:04.380 --> 00:00:06.420
You'll be looking at a familiar passage of Scripture.

00:00:06.420 --> 00:00:09.640
In fact, one that no doubt many of us

00:00:09.640 --> 00:00:13.239
have heard preached over the years, perhaps many times.

00:00:13.239 --> 00:00:15.779
In fact, I was commenting to Holly this afternoon

00:00:15.779 --> 00:00:18.479
about the passage and the message

00:00:18.479 --> 00:00:19.920
that I'd be preaching this evening

00:00:19.920 --> 00:00:24.120
that I think in 14 years plus, 14 and a half almost,

00:00:24.120 --> 00:00:27.739
I think I've only ever preached from this passage one time.

00:00:27.739 --> 00:00:30.940
I've heard many people preach on the passage,

00:00:30.940 --> 00:00:33.680
visiting missionaries, evangelists, and so on and so forth.

00:00:33.680 --> 00:00:37.860
But throughout this week, God just really burdened my heart

00:00:37.860 --> 00:00:39.939
from this passage of Scripture.

00:00:39.939 --> 00:00:44.380
And I believe tonight that I do not need to remind you

00:00:44.380 --> 00:00:46.939
that we live busy lives.

00:00:46.939 --> 00:00:47.779
Would you agree?

00:00:47.779 --> 00:00:49.619
You say, Pastor, I don't need that reminder.

00:00:49.619 --> 00:00:53.139
I am well aware of the fact that my life is busy.

00:00:53.139 --> 00:00:57.860
In fact, our region is one of the busiest places

00:00:57.860 --> 00:01:01.299
in America to live, really is.

00:01:01.299 --> 00:01:04.099
And I've had many people that have traveled here.

00:01:04.099 --> 00:01:06.620
I've had evangelists, and I've had missionaries,

00:01:06.620 --> 00:01:09.459
and I've had family members, and I've had friends

00:01:09.459 --> 00:01:12.540
that have traveled to this D.C. region,

00:01:12.540 --> 00:01:16.099
and they've said, I could never live here.

00:01:16.099 --> 00:01:18.699
I would have no interest in living

00:01:18.739 --> 00:01:23.339
in such a busy, fast-paced environment.

00:01:24.220 --> 00:01:26.339
We live in a busy place.

00:01:26.339 --> 00:01:27.699
We do.

00:01:27.699 --> 00:01:31.620
We were driving home from the wedding last night

00:01:31.620 --> 00:01:34.540
and got rerouted because wonderful 495

00:01:34.540 --> 00:01:36.180
is always under construction,

00:01:36.180 --> 00:01:40.099
and the time on the GPS is just gonna keep increasing

00:01:40.099 --> 00:01:41.540
and increasing and increasing,

00:01:41.540 --> 00:01:44.779
and so we got rerouted through D.C.,

00:01:44.779 --> 00:01:47.580
and it's almost, I don't know, close to 11 o'clock at night,

00:01:47.580 --> 00:01:51.180
and I'm like, where are all of these people going?

00:01:51.180 --> 00:01:52.580
Why?

00:01:52.580 --> 00:01:54.059
Do you ever feel like, why are they,

00:01:54.059 --> 00:01:56.419
like, I should be the only one driving right now

00:01:56.419 --> 00:01:57.980
because I wanna get somewhere,

00:01:57.980 --> 00:02:00.099
and they're impeding my progress.

00:02:00.099 --> 00:02:01.300
Have you ever felt that way?

00:02:01.300 --> 00:02:02.819
We get a little selfish, don't we?

00:02:02.819 --> 00:02:04.819
Like, why are they out?

00:02:05.779 --> 00:02:06.900
It was insane.

00:02:06.900 --> 00:02:10.619
I mean, just bumper to bumper, cars on top of cars,

00:02:10.619 --> 00:02:12.899
and literally cars on top of cars.

00:02:12.899 --> 00:02:14.580
I mean, it was crazy.

00:02:14.580 --> 00:02:16.660
We live in a busy place.

00:02:16.660 --> 00:02:18.419
We live busy lives,

00:02:19.339 --> 00:02:23.860
and we find that as we look at our schedules,

00:02:23.860 --> 00:02:26.779
there are times in which maybe we would come

00:02:26.779 --> 00:02:31.580
to the conclusion that I have more things to do

00:02:31.580 --> 00:02:33.699
than I have time to do them.

00:02:33.699 --> 00:02:35.619
Have you ever felt that way?

00:02:35.619 --> 00:02:40.419
I mean, just the list doesn't seem to get any shorter.

00:02:40.419 --> 00:02:42.940
It seems like you're adding things to the list

00:02:42.940 --> 00:02:46.179
before you can take things off of the list.

00:02:46.179 --> 00:02:47.979
Brother Jim Moore,

00:02:47.979 --> 00:02:49.899
he was here for our missions conference this year,

00:02:49.899 --> 00:02:51.539
he and his wife, Jim and Bonnie,

00:02:51.539 --> 00:02:53.699
and they flew to Germany.

00:02:53.699 --> 00:02:56.660
Actually, yeah, they flew to Germany on Wednesday,

00:02:56.660 --> 00:02:58.979
and we took them to the airport,

00:02:58.979 --> 00:03:00.699
and Brother Moore was commenting to me

00:03:00.699 --> 00:03:04.460
that Miss Bonnie gave him a list of three things

00:03:04.460 --> 00:03:05.940
that she wanted to have done

00:03:05.940 --> 00:03:08.179
before they left for their trip,

00:03:08.179 --> 00:03:10.460
and he said this as I'm driving him to the airport.

00:03:10.460 --> 00:03:12.779
He says, and you know, Brother Chris, you know what happened?

00:03:12.779 --> 00:03:15.460
There were about five more things added to that list

00:03:15.500 --> 00:03:16.740
that had to get done,

00:03:16.740 --> 00:03:20.220
and the original three are still not done.

00:03:20.220 --> 00:03:24.179
And it reminded me, that's sometimes how we live life,

00:03:24.179 --> 00:03:25.940
just busy.

00:03:25.940 --> 00:03:27.460
There's assignments that are due,

00:03:27.460 --> 00:03:29.619
there's meetings to go to,

00:03:29.619 --> 00:03:31.660
there's tasks to be accomplished,

00:03:31.660 --> 00:03:34.500
and we are forced to prioritize our schedules.

00:03:34.500 --> 00:03:37.699
Otherwise, we would simply be overwhelmed.

00:03:37.699 --> 00:03:40.020
There were days while I worked in the corporate world,

00:03:40.020 --> 00:03:42.000
and I've shared this with some of you personally

00:03:42.000 --> 00:03:45.279
and privately, that my daily schedule

00:03:45.279 --> 00:03:49.919
would have six to seven hours worth of meetings.

00:03:49.919 --> 00:03:51.679
How do you get anything done?

00:03:52.720 --> 00:03:55.559
Honestly, it's terrible.

00:03:56.679 --> 00:04:00.199
Sometimes we get into that frame of living

00:04:00.199 --> 00:04:02.399
and just being busy.

00:04:02.399 --> 00:04:04.399
I would say this tonight on the onset

00:04:04.399 --> 00:04:06.080
of reading the passage of Scripture,

00:04:06.080 --> 00:04:09.639
there is a danger in busyness

00:04:09.639 --> 00:04:14.360
that we must acknowledge and then must guard against.

00:04:15.240 --> 00:04:18.119
The passage is familiar in verse 38 of Luke 10.

00:04:18.119 --> 00:04:19.079
The Bible says this,

00:04:19.079 --> 00:04:23.160
now it came to pass as they went,

00:04:23.160 --> 00:04:28.000
that he, that's Jesus, entered into a certain village.

00:04:28.000 --> 00:04:33.000
A certain woman named Martha received him into her house.

00:04:34.959 --> 00:04:36.640
And she had a sister called Mary,

00:04:36.640 --> 00:04:39.239
which also sat at Jesus's feet,

00:04:39.239 --> 00:04:42.239
and heard his word.

00:04:42.239 --> 00:04:45.600
But Martha was cumbered about much serving,

00:04:45.600 --> 00:04:46.839
and came to him and said,

00:04:46.839 --> 00:04:51.200
Lord, dost thou not care

00:04:51.200 --> 00:04:55.679
that my sister hath left me to serve alone?

00:04:55.679 --> 00:04:59.239
Bid her therefore that she help me.

00:04:59.239 --> 00:05:02.000
And Jesus answered and said unto her,

00:05:02.000 --> 00:05:04.519
and I believe the tone that Jesus spoke to her

00:05:04.519 --> 00:05:07.640
in verse 41 was a tone of compassion.

00:05:08.600 --> 00:05:11.200
Martha, Martha.

00:05:13.200 --> 00:05:18.200
Thou art careful and troubled about many things.

00:05:19.359 --> 00:05:24.200
Verse 42, but one thing is needful.

00:05:24.200 --> 00:05:26.640
And Mary hath chosen that good part

00:05:26.640 --> 00:05:31.640
which shall not be taken away from her.

00:05:31.640 --> 00:05:33.320
I would submit to you this evening

00:05:33.320 --> 00:05:34.880
just by way of introduction

00:05:34.920 --> 00:05:39.920
that Martha and Mary knew who Jesus was.

00:05:40.440 --> 00:05:44.040
It was no secret to them that who showed up at their home

00:05:44.040 --> 00:05:45.559
on this particular occasion.

00:05:45.559 --> 00:05:48.160
In fact, if you read the Gospel of John,

00:05:48.160 --> 00:05:51.040
you understand that Mary and Martha and Lazarus,

00:05:51.040 --> 00:05:54.320
they were well acquainted with the Lord Jesus Christ.

00:05:54.320 --> 00:05:57.019
In fact, when Lazarus fell sick

00:05:57.019 --> 00:05:59.000
and they sent word to the master,

00:05:59.000 --> 00:06:00.839
they simply said this,

00:06:00.839 --> 00:06:05.279
he whom thou lovest is sick.

00:06:05.279 --> 00:06:10.119
We find that when Mary and Martha saw Martha being first,

00:06:10.119 --> 00:06:14.000
that Jesus was coming to the place where they were,

00:06:14.000 --> 00:06:18.200
that she has this perception, and I believe rightly so,

00:06:18.200 --> 00:06:22.220
if thou hadst been here, my brother would not die.

00:06:22.220 --> 00:06:24.519
You know, that reveals to us a measure

00:06:24.519 --> 00:06:28.679
about what she believed to be true about the person

00:06:28.679 --> 00:06:32.359
and power of the Lord Jesus Christ.

00:06:32.359 --> 00:06:35.839
She believed that he could have prevented

00:06:35.839 --> 00:06:37.799
the death of her brother.

00:06:37.799 --> 00:06:40.600
Mary utters the same exact words,

00:06:40.600 --> 00:06:43.839
knowing and revealing to us that they no doubt

00:06:43.839 --> 00:06:46.519
had been in some measure of conversation.

00:06:47.820 --> 00:06:49.700
Martha knew who Jesus was.

00:06:50.720 --> 00:06:53.760
This was not a situation that we read

00:06:53.760 --> 00:06:55.660
at the end of the Gospel of Luke

00:06:55.660 --> 00:06:58.739
where there are some disciples on the Emmaus Road.

00:06:58.739 --> 00:07:01.579
In fact, we just sang about that in our song,

00:07:01.579 --> 00:07:03.420
Yesterday, Today, and Forever.

00:07:03.420 --> 00:07:05.739
And those disciples on the Emmaus Road,

00:07:05.739 --> 00:07:09.140
when Jesus comes after the resurrection

00:07:09.140 --> 00:07:10.739
and begins to walk with them,

00:07:10.739 --> 00:07:15.739
they don't know who he is at the moment, right?

00:07:16.380 --> 00:07:18.859
And they invite him, he was gonna keep on going,

00:07:18.859 --> 00:07:20.700
but they invite him into the house

00:07:20.700 --> 00:07:24.899
and he comes into the house and when he broke bread,

00:07:24.899 --> 00:07:26.980
is that what the Bible says?

00:07:26.980 --> 00:07:28.260
Their eyes were open.

00:07:28.260 --> 00:07:32.619
And they said this, did not our heart burn within us

00:07:32.619 --> 00:07:35.700
while he spoke with us along the way?

00:07:35.700 --> 00:07:37.739
See, this is a different situation.

00:07:37.739 --> 00:07:39.579
Martha knew.

00:07:39.579 --> 00:07:42.640
She was aware of the fact that when Jesus came,

00:07:42.640 --> 00:07:44.260
as it says here in verse 38,

00:07:44.260 --> 00:07:47.079
that he entered into a certain village

00:07:47.079 --> 00:07:49.059
and a certain woman named Martha

00:07:49.059 --> 00:07:52.459
received him into her house.

00:07:52.459 --> 00:07:53.940
This evening, I wanna preach a message

00:07:53.940 --> 00:07:58.299
that I've simply entitled Too Busy for Jesus.

00:07:58.299 --> 00:08:01.140
Too Busy for Jesus.

00:08:01.140 --> 00:08:04.260
And before you turn me off this evening,

00:08:04.260 --> 00:08:07.920
I wanna let you know tonight that all of us

00:08:07.920 --> 00:08:12.179
can get to a place where we're too busy for Jesus.

00:08:12.179 --> 00:08:15.700
I don't think any one of us would ever say it.

00:08:15.700 --> 00:08:18.140
I don't think any one of us would stand up and say,

00:08:18.140 --> 00:08:20.899
I am too busy for Jesus.

00:08:20.899 --> 00:08:23.299
There are times, and I was actually speaking with Holly

00:08:23.339 --> 00:08:26.459
about a song, and the songwriter said

00:08:26.459 --> 00:08:30.179
that I'm filled with his work, but not with his word.

00:08:31.220 --> 00:08:35.919
Sometimes we can get so busy serving, which is good,

00:08:35.919 --> 00:08:38.099
but we forget who we're serving.

00:08:38.099 --> 00:08:41.239
We forget the importance of spending time with him.

00:08:41.239 --> 00:08:42.840
Amen?

00:08:42.840 --> 00:08:44.900
And so don't turn me off this evening.

00:08:44.900 --> 00:08:47.080
I hope that the message will be a help to you

00:08:47.080 --> 00:08:48.700
just as it's been to me.

00:08:48.700 --> 00:08:51.219
And just three observations from the text of Scripture.

00:08:51.219 --> 00:08:52.460
Again, a familiar passage,

00:08:52.460 --> 00:08:56.780
but I want you to notice number one, Martha received him.

00:08:56.780 --> 00:08:57.900
Martha received him.

00:08:57.900 --> 00:09:00.580
Notice what the Bible tells us in verse 38.

00:09:00.580 --> 00:09:05.340
The Bible says that Jesus, he came and as he traveled often

00:09:05.340 --> 00:09:07.619
and would go from village to village,

00:09:07.619 --> 00:09:12.099
it says that he came and he entered into a certain village,

00:09:12.099 --> 00:09:15.260
and it says this, a certain woman named Martha

00:09:15.260 --> 00:09:19.900
received him into her house.

00:09:19.900 --> 00:09:23.179
I appreciate the fact that God tells us

00:09:23.179 --> 00:09:27.179
that Martha received him into her house.

00:09:27.179 --> 00:09:30.820
I'm thankful for this important decision that Martha made.

00:09:30.820 --> 00:09:33.940
Actually, I believe tonight that if this decision

00:09:33.940 --> 00:09:37.780
of Martha to receive Jesus into her home was not made,

00:09:37.780 --> 00:09:39.799
we would not have the account.

00:09:40.820 --> 00:09:41.659
Amen?

00:09:41.659 --> 00:09:45.979
The only reason that we read verse 39, 40, and 41, and 42

00:09:45.979 --> 00:09:49.020
is because of the decision in verse 38.

00:09:50.059 --> 00:09:52.820
That Martha received him.

00:09:52.820 --> 00:09:55.940
Now, I want you to consider with me this evening

00:09:55.940 --> 00:09:58.580
the significance of this simple phrase

00:09:58.580 --> 00:10:00.580
at the end of verse 38 when the Bible.

00:10:00.580 --> 00:10:05.580
is that Martha received him into her house.

00:10:05.620 --> 00:10:08.740
I want you to, in your sanctified imagination this evening,

00:10:08.740 --> 00:10:11.160
I want you to picture the setting, if you will.

00:10:11.160 --> 00:10:14.820
I don't know that there was any announcement

00:10:14.820 --> 00:10:17.900
leading up to the arrival of the Lord Jesus Christ

00:10:17.900 --> 00:10:19.300
on this particular day.

00:10:19.300 --> 00:10:21.860
We understand that the communication capabilities

00:10:21.860 --> 00:10:26.660
were lacking in comparison to what we have today, amen?

00:10:26.660 --> 00:10:30.540
And we can communicate with people from far distances away

00:10:30.540 --> 00:10:32.380
and let them know that we're in route

00:10:32.380 --> 00:10:34.740
and let them know our expected arrival time,

00:10:34.740 --> 00:10:35.980
et cetera, et cetera.

00:10:35.980 --> 00:10:40.660
And we find that she received him into her house.

00:10:40.660 --> 00:10:43.300
I want you to think about the home and the setting,

00:10:43.300 --> 00:10:45.520
and I want you to consider with me

00:10:45.520 --> 00:10:48.560
the fact that Martha was willing to receive

00:10:48.560 --> 00:10:51.180
and Jesus comes in, what an opportunity.

00:10:51.180 --> 00:10:55.540
Jesus is God, amen?

00:10:55.540 --> 00:10:57.860
He is God in flesh.

00:10:57.900 --> 00:11:01.980
The word was made flesh and dwelt among us,

00:11:01.980 --> 00:11:04.140
according to John 1 in verse number 14.

00:11:04.140 --> 00:11:06.260
In the beginning was the word and the word was with God

00:11:06.260 --> 00:11:07.940
and the word was God or is God.

00:11:07.940 --> 00:11:11.620
And we understand this evening that Jesus is God.

00:11:11.620 --> 00:11:16.620
And we find this evening that God himself is in the home.

00:11:19.100 --> 00:11:21.140
This is amazing to me.

00:11:21.140 --> 00:11:25.540
I mean, what an opportunity as Martha would receive

00:11:25.580 --> 00:11:28.420
Jesus Christ into her home.

00:11:28.420 --> 00:11:31.340
And we find that not only did Martha receive him,

00:11:31.340 --> 00:11:34.020
but as we look at the text and we look at verse 40

00:11:34.020 --> 00:11:39.020
and verse 41, we find that number two, Martha served him.

00:11:40.020 --> 00:11:44.140
Can I tell you this evening that it's absolutely true

00:11:44.140 --> 00:11:47.340
that we are to serve the master.

00:11:47.340 --> 00:11:49.120
We have been saved to serve.

00:11:49.120 --> 00:11:50.980
Often you've heard it been said.

00:11:50.980 --> 00:11:54.380
And it's true, the Lord Jesus Christ has given us,

00:11:54.380 --> 00:11:57.500
we are his workmanship created in Christ Jesus.

00:11:57.500 --> 00:12:00.220
The Holy Spirit has given to every believer

00:12:00.220 --> 00:12:02.560
as he wills a spiritual gift.

00:12:02.560 --> 00:12:04.900
And we understand that we are to serve him.

00:12:04.900 --> 00:12:09.300
We are to be doing good works, not so that we can be saved,

00:12:09.300 --> 00:12:11.300
not so that we can stay saved,

00:12:11.300 --> 00:12:14.340
but because we are saved by the grace of God,

00:12:14.340 --> 00:12:17.620
we are to be serving the master.

00:12:17.620 --> 00:12:21.220
And by the way, I'd rather be a servant of righteousness

00:12:21.220 --> 00:12:22.820
than a servant of sin.

00:12:22.820 --> 00:12:25.420
And before you got saved and before I got saved,

00:12:25.420 --> 00:12:29.860
we were servants of sin, but now because of the change

00:12:29.860 --> 00:12:31.740
and because of the grace of God,

00:12:31.740 --> 00:12:35.380
we have the opportunity to serve the Lord.

00:12:35.380 --> 00:12:36.700
What a privilege.

00:12:37.620 --> 00:12:41.980
And Martha had received him and now Martha is serving him.

00:12:41.980 --> 00:12:45.020
Again, in my sanctified imagination in this evening,

00:12:45.020 --> 00:12:46.380
I want you to in your mind,

00:12:46.380 --> 00:12:48.780
you can see Martha running all over

00:12:48.780 --> 00:12:51.060
and trying to ensure that everything

00:12:51.060 --> 00:12:53.100
is just as it should be.

00:12:54.660 --> 00:12:56.240
Have you ever hosted a guest?

00:12:58.100 --> 00:13:01.460
You get so busy sometimes about all the details.

00:13:01.460 --> 00:13:02.660
You know what I'm saying?

00:13:02.660 --> 00:13:03.900
You got all these things going on.

00:13:03.900 --> 00:13:05.420
You wanna make sure everything's right in place

00:13:05.420 --> 00:13:06.780
and everything's like it should be.

00:13:06.780 --> 00:13:09.960
And serving is necessary and it's what we should be doing,

00:13:09.960 --> 00:13:13.580
but we must guard against being cumbered.

00:13:13.580 --> 00:13:16.660
The idea of the word cumbered means to be over occupied

00:13:16.660 --> 00:13:19.140
or to be too busy.

00:13:19.140 --> 00:13:21.180
The Bible says this in verse 40,

00:13:21.180 --> 00:13:25.840
but Martha was cumbered about much serving.

00:13:26.900 --> 00:13:31.900
I think it was obviously part of her personality

00:13:33.780 --> 00:13:36.140
and she's doing and she's serving

00:13:36.140 --> 00:13:37.780
and she's running here and there

00:13:37.780 --> 00:13:39.260
and she's doing all of these things.

00:13:39.260 --> 00:13:44.100
And as she's serving, she even pauses for a moment

00:13:44.100 --> 00:13:49.100
to go to the Lord and to say to the Lord,

00:13:49.380 --> 00:13:51.240
does thou not care that my sister

00:13:51.240 --> 00:13:52.980
hath left me to serve alone?

00:13:54.340 --> 00:13:56.780
I mean, she takes the moment to pause

00:13:56.780 --> 00:14:00.140
in all of her busyness to go to Jesus and say,

00:14:00.140 --> 00:14:02.700
don't you care that she's left me alone?

00:14:02.700 --> 00:14:06.820
Why don't you bid her therefore that she help me?

00:14:06.820 --> 00:14:08.020
Isn't that interesting?

00:14:12.060 --> 00:14:16.100
And Jesus says, Martha, Martha,

00:14:17.020 --> 00:14:21.780
thou art careful, full of care.

00:14:23.020 --> 00:14:23.860
That's what it means.

00:14:23.860 --> 00:14:26.180
The word careful here doesn't carry with it

00:14:26.180 --> 00:14:30.100
the idea that you're carefully placing something with care.

00:14:30.100 --> 00:14:31.680
No, it's full of care.

00:14:32.780 --> 00:14:36.100
And we find that he says that thou art careful

00:14:36.100 --> 00:14:40.680
and troubled about many things.

00:14:40.680 --> 00:14:43.460
We find this evening that Martha served him

00:14:43.460 --> 00:14:46.860
and again, serving the Lord is necessary,

00:14:48.060 --> 00:14:52.640
but we find that she was cumbered about much serving.

00:14:52.640 --> 00:14:55.800
There are times in our lives that we must remember

00:14:55.800 --> 00:15:00.340
who we are serving and not get so caught up

00:15:00.340 --> 00:15:02.920
in the fact that we're just serving.

00:15:03.800 --> 00:15:07.620
Today's October 26th and in about a month,

00:15:07.620 --> 00:15:09.000
we'll have Thanksgiving.

00:15:09.860 --> 00:15:13.100
In another month past that, we'll have Christmas.

00:15:13.700 --> 00:15:16.260
A tradition for us as Americans

00:15:16.260 --> 00:15:19.540
is oftentimes we gather together families.

00:15:20.580 --> 00:15:22.380
And we understand that there are some

00:15:22.380 --> 00:15:26.320
that have some sorrow during holidays

00:15:26.320 --> 00:15:28.260
and you wanna be careful of that,

00:15:28.260 --> 00:15:30.900
understanding various aspects,

00:15:30.900 --> 00:15:34.220
but we recognize that it's oftentimes

00:15:34.220 --> 00:15:37.420
that families will gather during the holidays.

00:15:37.420 --> 00:15:38.420
You know, it's interesting to me

00:15:38.420 --> 00:15:40.620
that as I began to think about this text of scripture,

00:15:40.620 --> 00:15:43.340
I began to even think about some family gatherings

00:15:43.340 --> 00:15:45.140
that I've had the opportunity to be part of

00:15:45.140 --> 00:15:46.540
and I'm thankful for,

00:15:46.540 --> 00:15:48.700
but there are times in which you gather together

00:15:48.700 --> 00:15:50.700
and you have this time together

00:15:50.700 --> 00:15:53.740
and someone's running around doing all this busy stuff

00:15:55.340 --> 00:15:58.120
and they forgot the person.

00:15:59.020 --> 00:16:00.740
They forgot the relationship.

00:16:00.740 --> 00:16:04.740
They forgot the fact that those things,

00:16:04.740 --> 00:16:06.500
yes, I want them to be done,

00:16:06.500 --> 00:16:10.600
but I wanna spend time with you,

00:16:10.600 --> 00:16:12.980
with the relationship.

00:16:12.980 --> 00:16:15.660
See, Holly sent me this text a few weeks,

00:16:15.660 --> 00:16:17.500
probably a couple months ago at this point.

00:16:17.500 --> 00:16:19.340
The only person that's gonna remember,

00:16:19.340 --> 00:16:21.040
in 20 years, the only person that's gonna remember

00:16:21.040 --> 00:16:24.140
that you worked overtime are your kids.

00:16:28.140 --> 00:16:28.980
Right?

00:16:32.740 --> 00:16:35.260
And we begin to think sometimes we can get so busy

00:16:35.260 --> 00:16:37.020
and make sure all these things are,

00:16:37.020 --> 00:16:38.820
and spiritually speaking,

00:16:40.020 --> 00:16:44.220
Martha, she's cumbered, she's too busy.

00:16:44.220 --> 00:16:49.220
She's in this place where she's over-occupied herself

00:16:49.860 --> 00:16:51.780
with all the things that need to be done

00:16:51.780 --> 00:16:55.700
and again, we find that the account is given to us first

00:16:55.700 --> 00:16:59.420
because she received him and then she served him.

00:17:00.560 --> 00:17:02.540
But I want you to notice in the text of scripture

00:17:02.540 --> 00:17:05.580
that God gives us a very important truth

00:17:05.580 --> 00:17:08.780
and it's the third point of our message this evening.

00:17:08.780 --> 00:17:10.700
Mary heard him.

00:17:12.060 --> 00:17:13.940
Martha received him.

00:17:13.940 --> 00:17:16.700
The Bible tells us in verse 38

00:17:16.700 --> 00:17:18.580
that he entered into a certain village

00:17:18.580 --> 00:17:21.540
and a certain woman named Martha received him

00:17:21.540 --> 00:17:23.340
into her house.

00:17:23.340 --> 00:17:24.740
She received him.

00:17:24.740 --> 00:17:26.500
She served him.

00:17:26.500 --> 00:17:29.320
But Mary, the Bible tells us, heard him.

00:17:30.320 --> 00:17:33.080
In verse 39, the Bible says this

00:17:33.080 --> 00:17:37.160
and she had a sister called Mary

00:17:37.160 --> 00:17:40.800
which also sat at Jesus' feet

00:17:40.800 --> 00:17:44.600
and heard his word.

00:17:46.920 --> 00:17:50.560
I think about the maniac of Gadara

00:17:51.920 --> 00:17:55.580
that was delivered from those demons that possessed him.

00:17:56.480 --> 00:17:59.200
And the Bible tells us that he was sitting,

00:18:00.040 --> 00:18:02.240
he was clothed, he was sitting in his right mind

00:18:02.240 --> 00:18:03.840
at the feet of Jesus.

00:18:03.840 --> 00:18:08.160
What a beautiful picture that God gives us.

00:18:08.160 --> 00:18:09.460
And I understand sometimes,

00:18:09.460 --> 00:18:11.120
and if you have a personality like mine,

00:18:11.120 --> 00:18:12.320
I like to be busy.

00:18:13.160 --> 00:18:14.720
I don't like downtime.

00:18:14.720 --> 00:18:16.840
I don't like that sort of thing.

00:18:16.840 --> 00:18:19.660
But sometimes we need to, as Jesus says to the disciples,

00:18:19.660 --> 00:18:20.640
come apart.

00:18:21.800 --> 00:18:23.720
You understand what I'm saying?

00:18:23.720 --> 00:18:26.480
And we find here that there are times

00:18:26.520 --> 00:18:30.600
in which we just need to sit at the feet of Jesus

00:18:30.600 --> 00:18:32.480
and just hear his word.

00:18:32.480 --> 00:18:34.900
And let his word minister to us.

00:18:34.900 --> 00:18:37.080
Let his word help us.

00:18:37.080 --> 00:18:40.679
We don't know the content of the message

00:18:40.679 --> 00:18:43.360
that Jesus spoke at this particular time.

00:18:43.360 --> 00:18:45.640
The Bible doesn't record it for us.

00:18:45.640 --> 00:18:47.239
In fact, as you study the Gospels,

00:18:47.239 --> 00:18:49.960
you'll find many times that the Bible doesn't record

00:18:49.960 --> 00:18:53.480
the entirety of the messages as Jesus would teach

00:18:53.480 --> 00:18:57.040
and preach, and the full messages are not captured

00:18:57.040 --> 00:18:58.960
for us in the Scriptures many times.

00:18:58.960 --> 00:19:02.440
But we find that Jesus was teaching.

00:19:02.440 --> 00:19:03.480
He's the master teacher.

00:19:03.480 --> 00:19:04.799
He's God.

00:19:04.799 --> 00:19:07.000
No one spoke like this man.

00:19:07.000 --> 00:19:11.119
He speaks as one that has authority.

00:19:11.119 --> 00:19:11.960
Because he does.

00:19:11.960 --> 00:19:14.520
All power is given unto me in heaven and in earth.

00:19:14.520 --> 00:19:15.980
He has all authority.

00:19:16.960 --> 00:19:19.840
And when he speaks, we ought to listen.

00:19:20.840 --> 00:19:25.000
The book of Proverbs uses terminologies

00:19:25.000 --> 00:19:27.520
about incline thine ear.

00:19:27.520 --> 00:19:29.880
Bow down thine ear.

00:19:29.880 --> 00:19:33.260
And sometimes when you read those words and those images,

00:19:33.260 --> 00:19:37.679
and I often think of us having that type of a response

00:19:37.679 --> 00:19:40.760
or that type of a perspective

00:19:40.760 --> 00:19:43.080
when we're hearing God's word.

00:19:45.000 --> 00:19:48.480
We find that as she's sitting there at the feet of Jesus,

00:19:48.480 --> 00:19:51.679
and as she's hearing the word,

00:19:51.679 --> 00:19:55.320
that Martha interrupts whatever it is that's being taught,

00:19:55.320 --> 00:19:57.040
whatever it is that Jesus is saying,

00:19:57.040 --> 00:19:59.239
because she comes in and she interrupts

00:19:59.239 --> 00:20:00.640
as we read a moment.

00:20:00.640 --> 00:20:02.360
to go on verse number 40 when she says,

00:20:02.360 --> 00:20:04.960
Lord, dost thou not care that my sister

00:20:04.960 --> 00:20:06.360
hath left me to serve alone?

00:20:06.360 --> 00:20:08.520
Bid her therefore that she help me.

00:20:08.520 --> 00:20:11.880
And the message, the lesson was interrupted

00:20:11.880 --> 00:20:15.680
by Martha at that moment and Jesus turns

00:20:15.680 --> 00:20:18.440
his attention to Martha, we've read verse 41,

00:20:18.440 --> 00:20:22.000
but I wanna draw your attention to what he says in verse 42.

00:20:22.000 --> 00:20:26.480
He told her that she was cumbered, she was careful,

00:20:26.480 --> 00:20:29.120
she was troubled about, notice what the Bible says

00:20:29.120 --> 00:20:33.000
at the end of verse 41, many things.

00:20:33.920 --> 00:20:37.080
And then Jesus says this in verse 42,

00:20:37.080 --> 00:20:41.760
but one thing is needful.

00:20:43.400 --> 00:20:48.400
One thing is needful and Mary hath chosen that good part,

00:20:53.600 --> 00:20:57.580
which shall not be taken away from her.

00:20:57.580 --> 00:20:59.220
You know what Jesus said?

00:21:00.580 --> 00:21:02.580
I'm not gonna tell her to come help you.

00:21:04.220 --> 00:21:06.140
Is that what he said?

00:21:06.140 --> 00:21:08.860
He didn't say it in those words, but in essence,

00:21:08.860 --> 00:21:12.580
the message that he gives Martha in response

00:21:12.580 --> 00:21:17.580
to her inquiry and to her request of don't you care

00:21:17.660 --> 00:21:19.460
that she's left me to serve alone?

00:21:19.460 --> 00:21:23.380
Bid her to help me and Jesus doesn't say no.

00:21:23.460 --> 00:21:27.540
Jesus teaches a lesson to Martha

00:21:29.000 --> 00:21:31.380
and in teaching Martha the lesson,

00:21:31.380 --> 00:21:36.380
not only would Martha receive life-changing truth,

00:21:37.580 --> 00:21:41.380
but I believe that the Lord has chosen to include

00:21:41.380 --> 00:21:45.700
this record of this, I don't even know how long

00:21:45.700 --> 00:21:50.060
of a visit it was in the holy scriptures

00:21:50.060 --> 00:21:54.740
to be a lesson for every child of God.

00:21:54.740 --> 00:21:57.180
One thing is needful.

00:21:58.940 --> 00:22:00.380
Many things.

00:22:03.820 --> 00:22:08.220
She's careful, she's troubled about many things.

00:22:08.220 --> 00:22:10.560
Can I tell you this evening that there are many things

00:22:10.560 --> 00:22:14.000
that pull us in all kinds of directions.

00:22:14.000 --> 00:22:16.820
There are many things that wanna find their way

00:22:16.820 --> 00:22:18.560
on your calendar and on mine.

00:22:19.560 --> 00:22:20.480
Amen?

00:22:20.480 --> 00:22:23.660
Many things, but one thing is needful.

00:22:24.620 --> 00:22:25.600
One thing is needful.

00:22:25.600 --> 00:22:28.320
Does it mean that we don't do any of those other things?

00:22:28.320 --> 00:22:29.720
It doesn't mean that.

00:22:29.720 --> 00:22:34.720
Here's a thought, Martha's serving, Mary's hearing.

00:22:36.400 --> 00:22:41.400
I, Martha, you, I am better equipped to serve him

00:22:43.000 --> 00:22:45.380
after I have heard him.

00:22:46.380 --> 00:22:51.380
I am better equipped, you are better equipped

00:22:52.380 --> 00:22:57.140
to serve him after you have heard him.

00:22:57.140 --> 00:22:59.060
Does that make sense tonight?

00:22:59.060 --> 00:23:02.360
Listen, there's a lot of things I can do.

00:23:02.360 --> 00:23:05.060
There's a lot of things you can do,

00:23:05.060 --> 00:23:10.060
but we must not forfeit our time with God.

00:23:11.220 --> 00:23:14.500
We must not neglect our time with God,

00:23:14.500 --> 00:23:15.900
but there's an assignment due.

00:23:15.900 --> 00:23:18.040
There's this pressure that's going on.

00:23:18.040 --> 00:23:20.900
There's this, no, no, your time with God

00:23:20.900 --> 00:23:23.620
is so absolutely vital.

00:23:24.700 --> 00:23:28.860
Jesus said, without me, you can do nothing.

00:23:30.140 --> 00:23:31.460
We need God.

00:23:32.780 --> 00:23:34.320
I would submit to you this evening

00:23:34.320 --> 00:23:37.580
that we need more time with God, not less time with God.

00:23:38.660 --> 00:23:41.940
I believe tonight that some of the statistics

00:23:41.940 --> 00:23:45.100
that we see throughout our society

00:23:45.100 --> 00:23:47.220
dealing with the amount of time

00:23:47.220 --> 00:23:48.840
that people spend in church,

00:23:48.840 --> 00:23:50.500
the amount of time that people

00:23:50.500 --> 00:23:53.420
that are professing Christians spend reading the Bible

00:23:53.420 --> 00:23:56.420
and in prayer, I believe that we're living in a day

00:23:56.420 --> 00:23:59.460
and an age where we have anemic Christians.

00:24:00.300 --> 00:24:02.380
We're just weak.

00:24:02.380 --> 00:24:03.900
Why?

00:24:03.900 --> 00:24:07.000
Because the strength comes by sitting at the feet of Jesus.

00:24:08.000 --> 00:24:12.480
The power comes through spending time with Jesus.

00:24:12.480 --> 00:24:13.360
That's where it comes.

00:24:13.360 --> 00:24:16.440
You think about those guys in Acts chapter number four

00:24:16.440 --> 00:24:19.280
when they're standing and they're being interrogated

00:24:19.280 --> 00:24:20.640
after they'd been imprisoned

00:24:20.640 --> 00:24:23.160
and Peter is called into question

00:24:23.160 --> 00:24:26.180
and begins to answer and to give a great proclamation

00:24:26.180 --> 00:24:28.900
about the truth that there's this man,

00:24:28.900 --> 00:24:31.040
he's not made whole by our own power,

00:24:31.040 --> 00:24:36.040
but by the power in the name of Jesus Christ of Nazareth.

00:24:36.320 --> 00:24:40.080
And after he professed and proclaimed that powerful truth

00:24:40.080 --> 00:24:41.720
that there's no other name under heaven

00:24:41.720 --> 00:24:44.280
given among men whereby we must be saved,

00:24:44.280 --> 00:24:48.000
that those religious leaders that heard

00:24:48.000 --> 00:24:52.160
and they were aware of the boldness of Peter and his answer,

00:24:52.160 --> 00:24:55.640
they perceived that they were ignorant and unlearned men.

00:24:56.680 --> 00:25:00.800
They'd been with Jesus and it made a difference

00:25:00.800 --> 00:25:02.520
because they'd been with Jesus.

00:25:03.520 --> 00:25:08.520
You cannot, I cannot substitute anything for time with Jesus.

00:25:15.480 --> 00:25:17.040
Ronnie, I'm gonna pick on him for a minute.

00:25:17.040 --> 00:25:19.440
He told me, pastor, I bought this book

00:25:19.440 --> 00:25:20.640
and I bought it yesterday

00:25:20.640 --> 00:25:21.820
and it has nothing to do with the Bible,

00:25:21.820 --> 00:25:23.120
but I want you to read it.

00:25:24.340 --> 00:25:27.480
It's about health and wellness and blah, blah, blah.

00:25:27.480 --> 00:25:28.600
I want you to read it, pastor.

00:25:28.600 --> 00:25:30.020
And I said, I got so many books

00:25:30.020 --> 00:25:31.280
on my reading list right now.

00:25:31.480 --> 00:25:33.820
I'm like two years deep in getting through the books

00:25:33.820 --> 00:25:35.840
on my reading list, honestly.

00:25:35.840 --> 00:25:37.860
I mean, I read books, I read books,

00:25:37.860 --> 00:25:40.400
but I just, I picked up a book last week to read it

00:25:40.400 --> 00:25:41.240
and I'm starting to read the book

00:25:41.240 --> 00:25:43.120
and I'm like, this is not my cup of tea.

00:25:43.120 --> 00:25:44.200
Have you ever read a book like that?

00:25:44.200 --> 00:25:46.420
You're like, man, it was just labor

00:25:46.420 --> 00:25:48.760
to get through a chapter and a half.

00:25:48.760 --> 00:25:50.960
And you know how many times I've picked it up since then?

00:25:50.960 --> 00:25:52.860
A big fat zero.

00:25:52.860 --> 00:25:55.600
It's still sitting next to my chair in my house

00:25:55.600 --> 00:25:57.940
and I'm probably not gonna pick it back up and read it.

00:25:57.940 --> 00:25:59.360
It's not my cup of tea.

00:26:00.200 --> 00:26:02.280
But then I have other books that are on my list

00:26:02.280 --> 00:26:03.720
that I'm gonna read.

00:26:03.720 --> 00:26:04.760
Here's what I told Ronnie.

00:26:04.760 --> 00:26:06.120
I told him this this morning.

00:26:06.120 --> 00:26:08.880
I said, Ronnie, how about you read the book

00:26:08.880 --> 00:26:10.300
and give me the summary?

00:26:11.760 --> 00:26:13.260
Isn't that a great idea?

00:26:15.880 --> 00:26:17.520
You can't do that with the Bible.

00:26:19.000 --> 00:26:20.640
You can't do that with the Bible.

00:26:23.700 --> 00:26:24.640
You can't fake it.

00:26:26.120 --> 00:26:28.560
You're either sitting at the feet of Jesus or you're not.

00:26:30.000 --> 00:26:30.840
Amen?

00:26:32.440 --> 00:26:37.400
And Jesus said to Martha, Martha, Martha,

00:26:38.500 --> 00:26:43.500
you're careful, you're troubled about many things.

00:26:45.080 --> 00:26:47.200
But one thing is needful.

00:26:48.400 --> 00:26:51.040
I want you to consider with me this evening

00:26:51.040 --> 00:26:55.200
that God himself was sitting,

00:26:55.200 --> 00:26:57.960
if I can use it this way tonight, in the living room.

00:27:00.360 --> 00:27:02.420
And she was too busy for Jesus.

00:27:04.560 --> 00:27:05.920
Am I telling you the truth?

00:27:07.140 --> 00:27:12.140
God himself was sitting in the living room.

00:27:12.600 --> 00:27:14.360
I understand they didn't have houses like we do,

00:27:14.360 --> 00:27:16.400
but just let me use the illustration.

00:27:17.840 --> 00:27:20.700
You can preach next week, not really.

00:27:24.200 --> 00:27:27.220
And she was too busy for Jesus.

00:27:28.220 --> 00:27:29.980
Can I tell you this evening?

00:27:32.700 --> 00:27:37.300
In a real sense, God is sitting in your living room

00:27:37.300 --> 00:27:42.300
and in my living room every day, every day.

00:27:44.700 --> 00:27:47.820
And he's just waiting for us to spend time with him.

00:27:47.820 --> 00:27:49.740
He's not gonna make you.

00:27:49.740 --> 00:27:52.760
He's not gonna force you, but he wants you to.

00:27:54.060 --> 00:27:56.620
He wants to have fellowship with you.

00:27:56.620 --> 00:27:58.420
